{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Enemy_Within",
  "title": "The Enemy Within",
  "summary": "In a grimy underworld cantina on Coruscant, the Jedi emissary Ikihsa Enb'Zik watches the volatile half-breed mercenary Arissa, also known as Captain Kiiko, whom he sensed touching the Force during an earlier Imperial Gala. Amid banter with the drunken spacer Juran, Enb'Zik approaches Arissa and offers to bring her to Ord Mantell to meet Luke Skywalker, warning that her latent abilities make her a target for the Sith. Wary and scarred by past betrayals, Arissa shares memories of being hunted by the Imperial Warlord Korolov, then abruptly draws a blaster and marches Enb'Zik to his ship, distrustful of a trap. Aboard his freighter, Enb'Zik reveals his identity and honorable intentions, removing his disguise to show he wears armor and offering to let her leave freely. Unknown to him, a dark Nightsister echo buried in Arissa's mind drives her to accept, intending to play the wounded prey and poison the Jedi from within. She extracts his personal oath of safe passage and agrees to accompany him.",
